<li><a href="#AuguLuciHumoDialEnga">4. Augustine; Lucian&rsquo;s Humorous Dialectical Engagement</a></li>
<li><a href="#TowaCiviPhilLifePicoEpigRichIII">5. Towards a &ldquo;Civil&rdquo; Philosophy: <em>Life of Pico</em>, <em>Epigrams</em>, <em>Richard III</em></a></li>
<li><a href="#SocrDialPhilCityUtop">6. Socratic Dialogue on Philosophy and the City: <em>Utopia</em></a></li>
<li><a href="#TrueDialTruePhilEspeAris">7. &ldquo;True dialectic and true philosophy, especially Aristotelian&rdquo;</a></li>
<li><a href="#FreeSpeeConsDialInqu">8. Free Speech, Conscience, and Dialectical Inquiry</a></li>
<li><a href="#JudgCons">9. Judgments &ldquo;in conscience&rdquo;</a></li>
<li><a href="#PoleWorkStatReasLibeLaw">10. Polemical Works: Status of Reason, Liberty, Law</a></li>
<li><a href="#ReasOughReigLikeKing">11. &ldquo;Reason ought to reign like a king&rdquo;</a></li>
<li><a href="#Bib">Bibliography</a>
   <ul>
