Archon Books.</li>

<li>Wegemer, Gerard B., 1996, <em>Thomas More on Statesmanship,</em>
Washington, DC: Catholic University of America Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, <em>Young Thomas More and the Arts of
Liberty</em>, New York: Cambridge University Press.
doi:10.1017/CBO9780511921834</li>
</ul>

<p>
The journal
 <a href="https://www.euppublishing.com/loi/more" target="other"><em>Moreana</em></a>
 (1963&ndash; ) is published biannually by the Association Amici
Thomae Mori and contains much important material.</p>

<h3 id="GBiblStud">G. Bibliographic Studies</h3>

<ul class="hanging">

<li>Boswell, Jackson Campbell, 1994, <em>Sir Thomas More in the
English Renaissance: An Annotated Catalogue</em>, Binghampton, NY:
Medieval and Renaissance Texts and Studies</li>

<li>Geritz, Albert J., 2000, <em>Thomas More: An Annotated
Bibliography of Criticism, 1935&ndash;1997,</em> Westport, CT:
Greenwood Press</li>

<li>Gibson, R. W., 1961, <em>St. Thomas More: A Preliminary
Bibliography of His Works and of Moreana to the Year 1750</em>, New
Have, CT: Yale University Press</li>

<li>Smith, Constance, 1981, <em>An Updating of R. W. Gibson&rsquo;s
<span class="plain">St. Thomas More: A Preliminary
Bibliography</span></em>, St. Louis, MO: Center for Reformation
Research</li>
</ul>
</div> 

